### Incorporating Local Traditions and Styles

Infusing local traditions into your wedding ceremony can add layers of meaning and create an authentic experience for you and your guests. In Malaga, a region rich in Spanish culture and history, there are numerous traditions that you can elegantly weave into your ceremony. One creative wedding idea is to include a traditional Spanish guitar performance or a flamenco dancer to entertain your guests during the reception, providing an unforgettable spectacle deeply rooted in Andalusian roots.**Traditional** oranges, a symbol of good luck, can be used as part of your table arrangements or as wedding favors, adding both a pop of color and cultural reference to your decor.

